    intro x
    simp [f.right_inv, g.right_inv]
```

The `simp` tactic is powerful enough to unfold the definitions of the ring isomorphisms and use the properties of the underlying ring homomorphisms (`map_add'`, `map_mul'`, `left_inv`, `right_inv`) to prove the goals directly. The key insight is that the composition of two isomorphisms preserves the ring structure and is itself an isomorphism.
